    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-10-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-10-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="536"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d536">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">834.156/243</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kreech</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Asunción</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-10-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 21, 1927</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received November 25.]</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 421</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to the Asunción Port Concession, I
                    have the honor to report that, on October 20th, the President signed the law,
                    passed at the last session of Congress, granting a concession to the Asunción
                    Port Concession Corporation.</p>
                <p>The Corporation’s representative, Mr. H. C. Mitchell, is obtaining the data
                    necessary for the drafting of plans and is attending to the preliminaries for an
                    early construction.</p>
                <p>There is a general feeling of optimism and the desire for American capital to
                    undertake the construction of a water works and sewage system, and needed
                    railway extensions.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Geo. L. Kreeck</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
